.TH "bee" "1" "2011-07-25" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee package management"
.SH "NAME"
bee \- Run a bee tool
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee "
.OP check
.OP init
.OP install
.OP list
.OP query
.OP remove
.I arguments
.YS
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
.B bee
is a wrapper tool that is used to run all bee tools. All options known by these bee tools can be passed
to
.BR bee .
.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-\-destdir <BEE_BEEDESTDIR>
Run
.B bee
as if
.B BEE_BEEDESTDIR
is your system's root directory. That means
.B BEE_BEEDESTDIR
is prepended to
.B BEE_METADIR
and
.B BEE_CACHEDIR
and in case you run
.BR bee\-install (1)
all files are extracted under
.BR BEE_BEEDESTDIR .
.TP
.B \-\-print-config
Dispays all bee relevant variables.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Prints a little help screen.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Prints bee's version.
.SH "FILES"
.TP
.B /etc/bee/beerc
.TQ
.B ~/.beerc
The main config files. Use these to change
.BR bee 's
environment variables.
.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B BEE_METADIR
.RS
Directory searched for installed bee packages
.P
Defaults:
.TQ
root-user: /usr/share/bee
.TQ
other:     ~/.local/share/bee
.RE
.TP
.B BEE_PKGDIR
.RS
Directory searched for available bee packages
.P
Defaults:
.TQ
root-user: /usr/src/bee/packages
.TQ
other:     ~/.local/src/bee/packages
.RE
